 Oldagram

Oldagram is a small front-end practice project that recreates a simple Instagram-style feed using 'HTML, CSS and JavaScript'.

It displays a list of posts from classic artists like 'Vincent van Gogh', 'Gustave Courbet' and 'Joseph Ducreux', with their avatars, locations, images, likes and comments.

The post data is stored in a JavaScript array and rendered on the page to create a clean, scrollable social-media style layout.

 Features

* Static feed layout (profile, post image, icons, likes and caption)
* Responsive image handling
* Simple, clean UI built with pure CSS
* All data managed from a single JavaScript file

 Tech used

* HTML
* CSS
* Vanilla JavaScript

This project was built as a learning exercise to practice layout, styling, and working with JavaScript data to generate UI content.


